<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 01 at 6:52PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY CONTINUES...
Light snow will continue this evening, with pockets of moderate snow
now moving into the area. Peak snowfall rates of a half inch per
hour may occur within these heavier bursts of snow. Reduced
visibilities to one mile and snow covered roads have been observed
and will continue through the evening with temperatures across the
area now at or below 32 F. Expect a slow commute and exercise
caution by slowing down and maintaining plenty of distance between
you and vehicles in front of you.</description>
